<HEADLINE> France and Portugal 1-1 after 90 Minutes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, June 28 (Xinhua) -- France and Portugal had to decide
the winner in extra time after a 1-1 scoring at 90 minutes of
their Euro 2000 semifinal on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Nuno Gomes gave Portugal a 1-0 lead over world champion in the
19th minute for his fourth goal of the championship.
</P>
<P>
France equalised in the 51st minute by Thierry Henry.
</P>
<P>
The winner plays either the Netherlands or Italy in Sunday's
final in Rotterdam, the Netherlands. 
</P>
</TEXT>
