<BODY>
<HEADLINE> France Sails into Final after "Golden Goal" </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, June 28 (Xinhua) -- France reached the final on
Wednesday as Zinedine Zidane's "golden goal" from a penalty gave
France a 2-1 win over Portugal in Euro 2000 Euro 2000 semifinal at
the King Baudouin Stadium.
</P>
<P>
In the 117th minute, Zidane striked the ball high in the left
top corner after Portuguese Abel Xavier handled the ball to keep
an angled shot.
</P>
<P>
Portugal took a first half lead when Nuno Gomes scored his
fourth goal of the championship in the 19th minute.
</P>
<P>
However, Thierry Henry equalized in the 51st minute from a
pass by Nicolas Anelka.
</P>
<P>
In the 90th minute, a spectacular reflex save off Fabien
Barthez on a header from Abel Xavier kept the French going into
extra time.
</P>
<P>
France plays either the Netherlands or Italy in the final on
Sunday in Rotterdam, the Netherlands.
</P>
<P>
In the second semifinal on Thursday, the Netherlands will play
Italy in Amsterdam's ArenA stadium. 
</P>
</TEXT>
