<DOCNO> XIE20000629.0016 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-29 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Peru to Use Ukrainian Helicopter against Locusts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The aircraft will join the spraying campaign of two Peruvian
army helicopters that have been spraying 400 kilograms of poison
in each passing over the affected area for one week.
</P>
<P>
The locust plague that affects the northern Andean departments
of Cajamarca, Lambayeque, Cuzco, and La Libertad has eaten more
than 5,000 hectares of crops.
</P>
<P>
The Agriculture Ministry said that the number of producers
affected by the insects is more than one thousand, a great
increase compared to the 800 registered in the last two days.
</P>
<P>
An enormous cloud of millions of insects moves and eats
hectares of cultivated land of corn, beans, peas, yucca, maracuya,
mango, and natural pastures in the most affected zones.
</P>
<P>
The Peruvian government declared recently the zones affected by
the insects into a state of phytosanitary emergency, as a
preventive measure.
</P>
<P>
The government allocated more than 300,000 dollars to combat
the locusts and ordered the intervention of two army battalions to
combat the plague with flamethrowers and hand-held fumigators.
</P>
<P>
The Agriculture ministry delivered to the agriculture producers
of the affected zones 20 tractors and 40 motorized sprayers for an
offensive from several fronts against the enormous locust cloud.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
