<HEADLINE> 2 Killed, 2 Injured in Car Crash in Egypt </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, June 29 (Xinhua) -- Two people were killed and two others
seriously injured on Thursday in a road accident in northern Egypt,
the state-owned Middle East News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The accident took place on the desert highway linking the
Mediterranean port city of Alexandria and the capital Cairo, when a
car overturned after running into a tree on the roadside, the news
agency quoted police as saying.
</P>
<P>
The driver, a 38-year-old engineer, and his 30-year-old wife
were injured while their five-year-old son and the husband's 65-
year-old mother were killed, police said.
</P>
<P>
The injured have been rushed to a hospital, and an investigation
is underway into the cause of the incident.
</P>
<P>
Road accidents are common in Egypt, where thousands of people
are killed or injured each year as a result of reckless driving and
negligence of traffic rules and regulations. 
