<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-29 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Nepal Ranks Low in Human Development Index: Report </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, June 29 (Xinhua) -- Nepal ranks 144 in terms of
human development out of 174 countries and regions included in the
Human Development Report 2000 commissioned by the United Nations
Development Program (UNDP).
</P>
<P>
Although Nepal's ranking is the same as last year, its Human
Development Index (HDI) value has increased to 0.474 from 0.463
last year, said Saraswathi Menon, resident representative of UNDP,
while launching the report here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Among Asian countries and regions, Nepal's HDI remains second
to Bangladesh from the bottom, according to the report.
</P>
<P>
"The report puts Nepal's poverty rate at 51.3 percent, one of
the eight countries in the world where more than half of the
population suffer from human poverty," said Menon.
</P>
<P>
Menon said that while the incidence of human poverty in Nepal
is the highest in South Asia, Nepal's income inequalities are vast.
</P>
<P>
"The poorest 20 percent of the population earn less than 8
percent of national income, while the richest 20 percent earn
nearly 50 percent," she said.
</P>
<P>
"In gender related development, Nepal is the only country in
the world where female life expectancy is lower than that of males,
" she said.
</P>
<P>
The report records that Nepal's female life expectancy is 57.6
years, while male's is 58.1 years. The average life expectancy in
Nepal is 57.8 years, which is 4.2 years lower than the average in
all south Asian countries.
</P>
<P>
While Nepal's male literacy is 62 percent, its female literacy
is only 28 percent, one of the lowest in the world, according to
the report.
</P>
<P>
"This reflects the low socio-economic status of Nepalese women,
who are more discriminated and marginalized, and are excluded from
many basic rights," said Menon.
</P>
<P>
Menon said concerted efforts have to be made to improve the
socio-economic status of women and other marginalized group.
</P>
<P>
"Human Development Report 2000 is a call to action on many
fronts: the importance of legal frameworks and the critical need
to focus on the most deprived, to name a few," she said.
</P>
<P>
UNDP's Human Development Index measures a country's
achievements in terms of life expectancy, educational attainment
and adjusted real income. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
