<HEADLINE> Russia Predicts End of Battle in Chechnya's Serzhen-Yurt </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, June 29 (Xinhua) -- Russia said Thursday that the
battle near the village of Serzhen-Yurt in southern Chechnya will
come to an end later Thursday after four days of fighting, with
most besieged Chechen rebels being wiped out.
</P>
<P>
The military operations conducted by the Russian forces near
the Chechen village of Serzhen-Yurt, where a large rebel group has
been surrounded, "will come to an end today," Russian Defense
Minister Igor Sergeyev told the press in Moscow Thursday morning.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Sergeyev denied the "heavy losses" on the part of
federal troops as reported by West media.
</P>
<P>
"There are some 150-200 fighters in this surrounded rebel group,
mainly Arab mercenaries, putting up a desperate resistance," he
said, confirming that the federal forces lost only 12 men in the
past three days of fighting but killed "scores of " rebels.
</P>
<P>
Sergeyev also denied reports by some foreign news agencies that
Chechen guerrillas had wiped out a Russian convoy near the village
of Yarysh-Mardy, killing 50 servicemen in the past 24 hours.
</P>
<P>
Russia's Interfax news agency on Thursday cited the
headquarters of the Russian forces in the North Caucasus as saying
that over 120 rebels have been killed in the fighting near Serzhen-
Yurt.
</P>
<P>
The Russian air forces have been keeping their attack on the
rebel group surrounded near Serzhen-Yurt, as the militants have
been trying to break through the federal encirclement, said the
headquarters.
</P>
<P>
"They suffered big losses to find there is no way to escape,"
said an officer at the headquarters.
</P>
<P>
The office of Sergei Yastrzhembsky, Russian presidential aide
on Chechnya, informed journalists that no Russian military losses
in Chechnya were reported over the past 24 hours.
</P>
<P>
The office also denied reports that large rebel formations have
concentrated outside Gudermes, the second biggest Chechen city,
describing this information as "untrue." 
</P>
</TEXT>
