<HEADLINE> China Sets up New Cellular Engineering Institute </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, June 29 (Xinhua) -- The Xi'an Cellular Engineering
Project Development Center was officially inaugurated today in
this capital of northwest China's Shaanxi Province. The state-
designated institute is expected to invigorate China's bio-
engineering research.
</P>
<P>
Jointly founded by the No. 4 Medical College of the Chinese
People's Liberation Army and the Shaanxi New and High-Tech
Industries Investment Co., the center will focus on the study of
engineering development of animal cells, cross-breeding tumor
cells, cellular-engineering and cell factor tests.
</P>
<P>
The institute, funded with venture capital from the investment
company, will become an incubator for important bio-engineering
programs and play a role in transforming scientific research into
products. 
</P>
</TEXT>
