<HEADLINE> Euro 2000 Referees Committee Backs Penalty Decision </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, June 29 (Xinhua) -- UEFA's referees' committee on
Thursday has backed match officials' decision to award the penalty
kick in favor of France in the Euro 2000 semifinal clash against
Portugal.
</P>
<P>
UEFA Referees' Committee member Volker Roth said in Rotterdam:
"It was a clear case of intentional handball which was seen by the
assistant referee, Igor Sramka.
</P>
<P>
"He called the referee's attention via the beeper system and
explained what he had seen. Guenter Benko correctly decided to
award a penalty."
</P>
<P>
France won 2-1 with the golden goal spot-kick converted by
Zinedine Zidane. 
