<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-29 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Coastal City to Host 12th International Fashion Festival </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 29 (Xinhua) -- The coastal city of Dalian in
northeast China's Liaoning Province will hold the 12th Dalian
International Fashion Festival on September 16-25.
</P>
<P>
At a news briefing this afternoon in Beijing, Sun Shiju, an
official from the festival's organizing committee, said that 11
programs including a grand opening ceremony, a garment exhibition,
an export fair and a fashion design contest and other activities
will be held during the festival.
</P>
<P>
The garment exhibition and the export fair will be held at the
city's Xinghai Convention and Exhibition Center which covers an
area of 15,000 sq m and has 710 standard booths.
</P>
<P>
More than 300 enterprises from China and overseas have applied
to participate in the first phase of the exhibition which runs
from September 16 to 19. The second phase will be held between 21
and 26.
</P>
<P>
Since 1988, Dalian has hosted 11 international fashion
festivals and achieved good economic and social results. The
business turnover of the 11th garment exhibition alone reached 5.
64 billion yuan (680 million US dollars).
</P>
<P>
The fashion festival has become a grand event which involves
trade, culture and tourism activities.
</P>
<P>
The 12th Dalian International Fashion Festival is jointly
sponsored by the China Council for the Promotion of International
Trade, the Chinese People's Association for Friendship with
Foreign Countries, the National Tourism Administration, the Hong
Kong Trade Development Council, the China National Textile Import
and Export Corporation, the Dalian Municipal People's Government
and 12 other work units. 
</P>
</TEXT>
