<HEADLINE> Chinese Premier Arrives in Berlin for Official Visit to Germany </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BERLIN, June 29 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Premier Zhu Rongji arrived
here Thursday for an official visit to Germany.
</P>
<P>
In a written statement delivered upon his arrival at
Schoenefeld Airport, the Chinese premier said his current visit is
aimed at further deepening the development of bilateral ties,
enhancing mutual understanding and trust as well as strengthening
cooperation.
</P>
<P>
He said in recent years, Sino-German relations have witnessed
an all-round development with closer cooperation in the fields of
economy, science and technology, culture, education and
environment protection.
</P>
<P>
"We are satisfied with the good development of bilateral ties
and are optimistic over their future prospect," he said.
</P>
<P>
Zhu noted that both China and Germany are influential countries
in the world and are playing important roles in international
affairs.
</P>
<P>
The two countries should strengthen their cooperation and
establish a comprehensive partnership which is in the common and
long-term interests of both countries, he said.
</P>
<P>
Germany is the second leg of the premier's tour of six European
nations and the European Union headquarters. He has visited
Bulgaria and will also travel on to Luxembourg, the Netherlands,
Italy and Belgium. 
