<HEADLINE> Guangzhou-HK Optical Network Operational </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, June 29 (Xinhua) -- The second-phase optical network
linking 10 cities in south China's Guangdong province, including
Guangzhou and Shenzhen, with Hong Kong, became operational today.
</P>
<P>
Early this year China Telecom invested 60-million yuan (7.2
million US dollars) for the optical project.
</P>
<P>
The network is aimed to substantially improve the long-distance
telephone capacity between Guangdong Province and the
international metropolis of Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
The optical network with a bandwidth of 15GB can allow 360,000
people to make calls simultaneously. The 1,095 km long optical
fiber can also accommodate new telecom services, such as ATM
network and IP. 
</P>
</TEXT>
