<HEADLINE> Website for Chinese Women Launched </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 29 (Xinhua) -- cwow.com, a website specialized
in providing information for Chinese women, was launched here
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
cwow, the abbreviation of "Chinese women on the web," featuring
three major sections -- relationship, wedding and parenting,
covers several important stages in a woman's life, according to
Angeline Chow and Patricia Tung, co-founders of the website.
</P>
<P>
Headquartered in Hong Kong with branch offices in Taiwan and
the United States, cwow provides over 25 interactive applications
and local resources for making planning and purchase decisions.
</P>
<P>
WOW Networks Limited, cwow.com's parent company, is funded by
NASDAQ-listed chinadotcom corporation and Partners-E Incorporated,
a private Internet and technology investment fund. 
