<HEADLINE> Li Peng Meets Russian Duma Delegation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 29 (Xinhua) -- Li Peng, chairman of the Standing
Committee of the National People's Congress (NPC), told a senior
member of the State Duma of the Federal Assembly of Russia here
today that China pays great attention to its friendly relations
with Russia and believes the relations will grow further.
</P>
<P>
Li said during a meeting with Dmitry Rogozin, chairman of the
International Affairs Committee under the Duma, and his party, who
arrived here on June 25 at the invitation of the NPC's Foreign
Affairs Committee, that China-Russia relations will have new
development under the joint efforts from both sides.
</P>
<P>
"China-Russia relations have grown rapidly over the past few
years," he said. "We have scored remarkable achievements in the
cooperation in areas of politics, economy and trade, science and
technology and international affairs as the state leaders of our
two countries exchanged visits frequently."
</P>
<P>
Russian President Vladimir Putin, since taking office, has
repeatedly said that Russia will continue to push forward its
strategic cooperative partnership with China. The Chinese side
highly values his remarks and believes China-Russia relations will
develop to new highs under the joint efforts of both sides, Li
said.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the Chinese parliament chairman said that both
China and Russia support building a mutli-polarized world instead
of a single-polarized one, adding that single-polarization is a
dangerous trend, and harmful to world peace.
</P>
<P>
China and Russia also oppose the deployment of national missile
defense system (NMD) by the United States, he noted. The
deployment of NMD is a concept inherited from the Cold War
mentality, and is threatening world peace.
</P>
<P>
Rogozin said Russia and China share the same stand and attitude
on many issues. He stressed that he hopes the two countries and
parliaments of the two strengthen their cooperation in various
areas.
</P>
<P>
The Russian chairman said he and his delegation were deeply
impressed with the changes in China after the country adopted the
policy of reform and opening to the outside world.
</P>
<P>
Chairman of NPC Foreign Affairs Committee Zeng Jianhui, Vice-
Minister of Foreign Affairs Ji Peiding, and Russian Ambassador to
China Igor A. Rogachev were present at the meeting. 
</P>
</TEXT>
