<HEADLINE> Kuala Lumpur Stocks Close Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, June 29 (Xinhua) -- Share prices on the Kuala
Lumpur Stock Exchange closed lower Thursday following the
shortlived support from investors to lift the market higher.
</P>
<P>
At the close, the 100-quality stocks Composite Index dropped 11.
29 points to 830.25, the all-share Emas Index fell 2.77 to 206.96,
the Industrial Index lost 2.03 points to 1,446.25 while the Second
Board Index edged up 0.18 of a point to 217.11.
</P>
<P>
Losers led gainers by 407 to 267 while 157 counters were
unchanged and 157 counters untraded.
</P>
<P>
The day's total turnover increased to 225.811 million shares
worth 721.325 million ringgit (189.82 million U.S. dollars) from
200.221 million shares valued at 872.685 million ringgit (229.65
million U.S. dollars) on Wednesday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
