<HEADLINE> World Marketing Conference to Help Thai Businessmen </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, June 29 (Xinhua) -- The third World Marketing
Conference, which is being held here from June 29 to 30, is
believed to help Thai businessmen to enhance their competitiveness
in the world market, a Thai marketing expert said here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
"This is a good opportunity for Thai businessmen to share the
marketing experiences with international colleagues, and upgrade
their marketing skills," Supat Tansathitikorn, the chief organizer
of the meeting and a local marketing expert, told Xinhua after the
opening ceremony of the two-day forum.
</P>
<P>
About 1000 marketing experts, marketing managers and business
executives from Thailand and other parts of the world are
attending the meeting.
</P>
<P>
The speakers at the meeting include experts and executives from
world's top companies such as the Microsoft, the Compaq Computer,
the Motorola and the Coca-Cola.
</P>
<P>
Supat, who is also the honorary chairman of the Marketing
Association of Thailand, said, "We hope this conference will help
the Thai businessmen and marketing professionals to become more
market-oriented, and well-equipped with ideas to map out their
global marketing plan."
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, the participants will focus on the issue of
how to develop advanced marketing strategies to stay ahead of the
challenging competition at the regional and world level, according
to him.
</P>
<P>
Topics such as on-line marketing, marketing innovation, image
marketing and marketing management are also on the agenda, he said.
</P>
<P>
The world marketing conference is a biennial international
meeting sponsored by the World Marketing Association, and the
first meeting was held in Chicago, the United States, in 1996.
</P>
<P>
Next meeting will be hosted by Singapore two years later.
</P>
</TEXT>
