<HEADLINE> Australia Wins Oceania Nations Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, June 29 (Xinhua) -- Australia beat New Zealand 2-0 in
the final to win the Oceania Nations Cup in Papeete, Tahiti on
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Shaun Murphy opened the scoring in the 41st minute while Craig
Foster headed home the second goal in the 66th.
</P>
<P>
By winning the tournament, Australia qualified to represent
Oceania at the 2002 Confederations Cup.
</P>
<P>
The Solomon Islands overcame a one-goal deficit at halftime to
beat Vanuatu 2-1 in the third-place play-off. 
</P>
