<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Stocks Fall 0.92 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 29 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong stocks closed lower
Thursday due to profit-taking activities triggered by the U.S.
Federal Reserve's decision to leave interest rates unchanged.
</P>
<P>
The Hang Seng Index fell 151.62 points, or 0.92 percent, to
close at 16,286.80, with the turnover of 11.178 billion HK dollars
(1.433 billion U.S. dollars), compared to Wednesday's volume of 11.
280 billion HK dollars (1.446 billion U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The blue chips opened up 35.98 points at 16,474.40 in the
morning. The gains was soon offset by investors' profit taking on
their recent gains, and expiry of June futures also prompted
selling pressure in the stocks, said traders.
</P>
<P>
All sub-indices of Finance, Utilities, Properties, Commerce and
Industry lost by 0.30 percent, 1.23 percent, 2.41 percent and 0.82
percent, respectively.
</P>
<P>
China-related stocks ended lower with the Hang Seng China
Enterprises Index down 2.14 percent and the Hang Seng China-
Affiliated Corp Index down 0.73 percent.
</P>
<P>
The Hang Seng IT Index and the Hang Seng IT Portfolio Index
also declined by 0.39 percent and 0.24 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
