<HEADLINE> HKSFC Sets Up Investment Education Website </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 29 (Xinhua) -- The Hong Kong Securities and
Futures Commission (HKSFC) Thursday launched the Electronic
Investor Resources Center, a website aimed to educate investors to
help them make informed investment decision.
</P>
<P>
The launch of the website -- www.hkeirc.org, unlike other
financial portals, does not give investment advice. It is
dedicated to empowering investors to acquire knowledge on the
different aspects of investing.
</P>
<P>
Targeting at investors with different investing profiles, the
center is designed as a virtual library covering a wide range of
topics.
</P>
<P>
It is linked to over 400 websites of regulators, market
institutions and Internet content providers.
</P>
<P>
New links will be added to each section on an ongoing basis in
order to keep investors abreast of new developments and references.
</P>
<P>
HKSFC Chairman Andrew Sheng said the center is a cost effective
and easily accessible way for the investors to get hold of timely
and good quality information.
</P>
<P>
"As markets become more complex, investors must evaluate their
own risk appetite and understand and appreciate the risks of their
investments," he said.
</P>
<P>
Sheng hoped that more and more investors would take advantage
of this new website.
</P>
<P>
Stephen Ip, secretary for financial services of the Hong Kong
Special Administrative Region, officiated the launch of the center.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
