<HEADLINE> Former UNESCO Assistant Director-General Dies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 29 (Xinhua) -- Yang Tianquan, former assistant
director-general of the United Nations Educational, Scientific and
Cultural Organization (UNESCO), died of illness in Shanghai on
June 24. He was 83.
</P>
<P>
Yang was also a member of the Sixth, the Seventh and the Eighth
National Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative
Conference, the top advisory body of China.
</P>
<P>
Yang received a Ph.D. in philosophy at a New York university in
1949. He was later appointed a budget administrator, the budget
bureau chief and the assistant director-general of the UNESCO. He
had made positive contributions to promoting cooperation between
UNESCO and China. 
</P>
