<HEADLINE> France Telecom to Sell Part of Internet Group on Stock Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 29 (Xinhua) -- The French telecommunications
monopoly France Telecom will turn 9.7 percent of the capital of
its affiliate internet group, Wanadoo, into stocks to be listed at
Paris Bourse (stock market), the company said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The price of each Wanadoo stock is fixed at 17-20 euros (about
16.15-19 U.S. dollars) and the stock will be formally listed at
the Paris Bourse on July 18, said France Telecom. The offer of the
sale of the stocks will be launched on June 30.
</P>
<P>
If the market accepts the price of the stock, the total value
of Wanadoo will stand at 17-20 billion euros (about 16.15-19
billion dollars).
</P>
<P>
Michel Bon, the president of Wanadoo, said that up to 1 million
people could be interested in buying the Wanadoo stocks.
</P>
<P>
Wanadoo is driving away at publicizing its stocks in the market
as two other major French corporations -- Vivendi Environment as
well as European Airspace, Defense and Space (EADS) -- will also
introduce their stocks to the market in July. 
</P>
</TEXT>
