<HEADLINE> French Serial Killer Suspect Commits Suicide in Portuguese Jail </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 29 (Xinhua) -- French serial killer suspect Sid
Ahmed Rezala committed suicide Wednesday night in a Portuguese
prison where he has been detained for six months, said the French
Ministry of Justice on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Rezala, a Frenchman of Algerian origin who used to live in
Marseille, was reportedly killed in a fire in his individual cell
in a Lisbon prison, said French and Portuguese officials.
</P>
<P>
He was suspected to have killed two women on two night trains
in France last October and murdered another woman in the northern
French city of Amiens.
</P>
<P>
Rezala was arrested in January in the suburb of Lisbon by
Portuguese police after several months on the run in France and
Spain.
</P>
<P>
The suicide took place when the Portuguese judicial authorities
were making a final decision on whether to extradite him to France
or not.
</P>
<P>
Rezala could be sentenced to 30 years in prison if convicted of
his crimes under the French law. 
</P>
</TEXT>
