<HEADLINE> China's First Website on Currency Opens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 29 (Xinhua) -- China has opened the country's
first currency website-- www.chinamoney.com.cn.
</P>
<P>
The website, created by the China Foreign Exchange Center and
an inter-bank lending center, provides information on foreign
exchange market, bonds, and inter-bank lending.
</P>
<P>
The China Foreign Exchange Center has opened three price
quoting systems to customers and e-mail addresses to nearly 5,000
financial institutions. The center has also developed on-line
communication software for the financial institutions.
</P>
<P>
The website lays the foundation for monitoring agencies to set
up an electronic system of monitoring the whole currency market in
China, experts say.  
</P>
