<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Emergency Yet to Result in Stop to Violence in Ambon, Indonesia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Explosions and sporadic gunfire were still heard coming from
Batugantung, Kampung Kolam and Nusaniwe areas in Ambon on Thursday,
according to the Antara News Agency.
</P>
<P>
In many parts of Ambon city, people were still terrorized by
sniper activity. Snipers shooting from storied buildings were
continuing to operate in the Batugantung, Mardika, Batu Merah,
Talake and Sirimau areas.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that the security forces have intensified their
patrols in conflict-prone areas.
</P>
<P>
An undetermined number of Ambon residents, mostly women and
children, who had fled their homes, was reported to be still
staying at self-made refugee camps in the hills just outside the
city.
</P>
<P>
The state of civil emergency came into effect in Maluku and
North Maluku provinces at midnight on Monday.
</P>
<P>
President Abdurrahman Wahid declared the emergency in order to
stop the 18-month-old conflict between Muslims and Christians.
</P>
<P>
The renewed communal clashes in Ambon has so far left at least
70 people dead over seven consecutive days of fighting since June
21 and hundreds of others injured. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
