<HEADLINE> US Firm Brady Goes into Production in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 29 (Xinhua) -- A subsidiary of U.S. sign and
label maker Brady Corp. has gone into operation in Wuxi City, east
China. It will manufacture products for telecommunications
companies such as Motorola, Nokia and Shanghai Bell.
</P>
<P>
The new company, located in the Singapore Industrial Park in
Wuxi, Jiangsu Province, is exclusively owned by Brady, with an
investment of five million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
It is Brady's first production base in China and Brady
considers China as an important market, said Katherine Hudson, CEO
of Brady.
</P>
<P>
It will manufacture labels, bar codes for portable printers and
software, die cutting materials for telecommunication, as well as
special tapes and wire cable signs for aviation technology and
anti-fake equipment, she said.
</P>
<P>
Brady, whose headquarters is in Wisconsin, has set up
representative offices in Hong Kong, Beijing, Shanghai and
Shenzhen over the past decade. 
</P>
