<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-29 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanghai Punishes Drug Traffickers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 29 (Xinhua) -- A railway court in Shanghai has
sentenced a drug trafficker to death with a two years' probation.
</P>
<P>
Zhao Xianhui, a farmer from southwest China's Yunnan Province,
was found guilty of smuggling drugs from neighboring Myanmar to
China with four other accomplices.
</P>
<P>
On August 14 last year, Zhao and the four men put 699.8 grams
of heroin packed in condoms and concealed them in their anus. They
were tracked down by railway policemen on the train.
</P>
<P>
Last week, the four were sentenced to 15 years in prison,
stripped of political rights for three years and confiscated
personal property worth 5,000 yuan (about 600 US dollars) each.
</P>
<P>
Two other farmers from southwest China's Guizhou Province, Feng
Meng and Luo Diwen, were found taking drugs and carrying 591.5
grams of drugs on a train from Kunming to Shanghai on November 29
last year.
</P>
<P>
Last week, they were sentenced to death for transporting drugs.
The court also confiscated their property worth 30,000 yuan each.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
