<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Cracks Down on Fake and Shoddy Steel Products </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 29 (Xinhua) -- China has launched a nationwide
campaign to crack down on fake and shoddy steel products to
guarantee construction quality and prevent potential accidents.
</P>
<P>
The State Administration of the Metallurgical Industry and the
State Bureau of Quality and Technical Supervision held a televised
conference Wednesday, urging local administrations to improve
their efforts in fighting against fake products.
</P>
<P>
In recent years, production and sales of fake and shoddy steel
products have been common in some regions, especially for steel
products used in construction.
</P>
<P>
A survey shows that China has 1,000-plus illegal steel plants,
producing more than 5 million tons of substandard steel each year.
</P>
<P>
Li Chuanqing, director of the State Bureau of Quality and
Technical Supervision, said that local administrations must stop
providing temporary production licenses to small iron and steel
plants that will close down sooner or later. 
</P>
</TEXT>
