<HEADLINE> China's Airports Competing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 29 (Xinhua) -- Competition attracting passengers
and cargo between neighbouring airports has emerged in China, due
to the rapid development of expressway network shortening the
distance between them.
</P>
<P>
For instance, the airports of Tianjin and Beijing, Nanjing and
Shanghai, Zhuhai and Macao, and Chongqing and Chengdu, have
started to compete for more business.
</P>
<P>
An insider noted that the competition will result in
significant improvement of airport service.
</P>
<P>
But it will not cause price competition, since airlines and
airports mustn't change the current prices, which have been
defined by the Civil Aviation Administration of China, he said.
</P>
<P>
</P>
