<HEADLINE> China's Airlines Improving Cargo Transport Business </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 29 (Xinhua) -- China's airlines have been
introducing more cargo planes or transferring passenger planes to
carrying cargo, due to the significant increase of cargo transport
business recently.
</P>
<P>
Air China plans to invest in cargo business, while postponing
its purchase of passenger planes.
</P>
<P>
China Cargo Airlines will also assemble the third MD-11 cargo
plane in August, with which the carrier will increase the flights
to Hong Kong, Southeastern Asia, the United States and Europe.
</P>
<P>
China Southern Airlines also plans to introduce B747-400 cargo
planes flying on the Shenzhen-Chicago route.
</P>
<P>
China Southern Airlines President Yan Zhiqin revealed that his
company will also establish an international cargo transport
center in Shenzhen, developing international long-distance cargo
service.
</P>
<P>
Yan predicted that China's cargo transport market will maintain
an annual growth rate of over 10 percent in the next ten years.
