<HEADLINE> Body of Former Vice-Premier Cremated </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 29 (Xinhua) -- The body of former Chinese Vice-
Premier Geng Biao was cremated at the Babaoshan Cemetery for
Revolutionaries in Beijing today.
</P>
<P>
Geng, also former vice-chairman of the Standing Committee of
the sixth National People's Congress, died of illness on June 23
at the age of 91.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Vice-President Hu Jintao and Vice-Premier Li Lanqing
were present at today's funeral service.
</P>
<P>
Geng was described as an outstanding member of the CPC, a tried
and loyal Communist fighter and a proletarian revolutionary,
military strategist and veteran Chinese diplomat.
</P>
<P>
He joined the Communist Party of China (CPC) in 1928, and was a
member of the Political Bureau of the 11th CPC Central Committee.
</P>
<P>
During Geng's illness and after his death, China's top leaders
Jiang Zemin, Li Peng, Zhu Rongji, Li Ruihuan and Wei Jianxing
visited him or sent messages of condolence to his relatives.
</P>
