<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-29 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Cultivates Colored Hot Peppers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, June 29 (Xinhua) -- Hot pepper is basically green or red,
but a Chinese company has succeeded in cultivating a variety of
colored peppers.
</P>
<P>
In the Fengle Seeds Industry Company laboratory in east China's
Anhui Province, you can find white, purple, yellow and black hot
peppers. Even in one plant you can have hot peppers in several
colors.
</P>
<P>
Dai Zuyun, an agriculture scientist, said that no other
companies in China has been successful in cultivating such
colorful hot peppers, although the Netherlands, Spain, Bulgaria
and Israel have been successful in cultivating different colored
hot peppers as well.
</P>
<P>
The company has tried to introduce foreign varieties in China,
but attempts have failed as China's climate, soil, and infestation
of insects are different from those of other countries.
</P>
<P>
Nevertheless, the company started to develop its own technology.
After three years of experiments, it finally succeeded in planting
different colored hot peppers using hybrid and directive breeding
techniques.
</P>
<P>
Dai said colored hot peppers are a kind of cash crop which are
not only edible but also ornamental. In south China's Hainan
province, a kilogram of colored hot peppers are sold for 17 yuan (
about two US dollars), he said.
</P>
<P>
The company has started to supply colored hot pepper strains to
Shaanxi, Guangdong, Yunnan, Hainan and Anhui provinces.
</P>
<P>
Experts predicted that colored hot peppers will have a bright
future on the domestic market. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000629.0236 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-29 </DATE_TIME>
