<HEADLINE> Framatome to Aid China in Making Nuclear Valves </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 29 (Xinhua) -- A Chinese company based in
Shanghai will produce valves for nuclear power plants with the
assistance of France's Framatome.
</P>
<P>
The Shanghai Lianggong Valve Factory has reached an agreement
with Framatome recently, becoming the firm Chinese enterprise to
use foreign technology in producing valves for nuclear power
plants.
</P>
<P>
Under the agreement, Framatome will provide technical
assistance to help the Shanghai factory design and produce valves.
The valves will comply with French nuclear equipment production
standards.
</P>
<P>
Valves are important to the nuclear safety, widely used in
nuclear power plants.
</P>
<P>
Framatome, a leading nuclear power equipment manufacturer in
the world, is the major contractor of Daya Bay and Ling'ao nuclear
power plants in southern China.
</P>
<P>
Late last year, Framatome reached an agreement to cooperate
with Shanghai Automation Instrumentation Co. Ltd. 
