<DOCNO> XIE20000629.0237 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-29 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Nepal's Health Status Ranks 150th in World: Report </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The total government expenditure on health is only 26 percent
in Nepal while total private expenditure stands at 74 percent,
which is significantly higher compared to some 25 percent in
industrial countries, said the World Health Report 2000.
</P>
<P>
Nepal spends as low as 3.7 percent of its GDP on health, said
the report, the first ever analysis of the world's health systems
carried out by WHO.
</P>
<P>
The report recorded average life expectancy of a Nepali woman
at 57.8 years while that of a man at 57.3 years, compared with an
average level of over 70 years in developed countries.
</P>
<P>
Nepal's health system is not so responsive but a positive note
is that the government has made attempts to provide the health
services to the outlying districts, the report said.
</P>
<P>
WHO's assessment system is based on five indicators: overall
level of population, health indisparities within the population,
overall level of health system responsiveness (a combination of
patient satisfaction and how well the system acts), distribution
of responsiveness within the population and the distribution of
financial burden within the population. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000629.0238 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-29 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Indonesian House Passes Motion for Interpellation of President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The motion gained 332 votes, rejected by 63 votes and 36 votes
abstains. A majority of votes in the 500-seat House is needed for
the motion to be accepted.
</P>
<P>
The motion, supported by the Indonesian Democratic Party of
Struggle (PDI-P) and the Golkar Party, is aimed at summoning and
seeking an explanation from the president over the dismissal of
State Minister of Investment and State Enterprises Development
Laksamana Sukarni and Minister of Trade and Industry Yusuf Kalla.
</P>
<P>
Laksamana is high up in the ranks of PDI-P while Kalla is a
Golkar Party senior member.
</P>
<P>
PDI-P faction chairman Arifin Panigoro maintained that the
interpellation was not aimed at questioning the president's
prerogative to dismiss the ministers, but on the grounds of making
such a hasty decision.
</P>
<P>
"It is aimed at questioning the inconsistency of the reasons
stated by the president for the ministers' dismissal," he said.
</P>
<P>
The president earlier said that the replacement of Laksamana
and Kalla on April 25 was aimed at harmonizing his economics team.
But later, the president, during a closed-door consultative
meeting with House leaders, claimed that they were axed because
the two were allegedly involved in graft. 
</P>
</TEXT>
