<HEADLINE> Xinhua World Economic News Summary at 0430 GMT, June 29 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS -- The Bank of Greece, the country's central bank,
Wednesday reduced its key intervention rates by between 0.50 and 0.
75 basis points.
</P>
<P>
The central bank reduced the weekly intervention rate for two-
week funds from 8.75 percent to 8.25 percent while the primary
overnight lending rate was cut by 0.75 percentage point from 8.0
percent to 7.25 percent. It is the sixth such reduction in eight
months with the aim of bringing the country's short-term rates
closer to their European Union equivalents. (Greece-Bank)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
