<HEADLINE> Brazil, Uruguay Draw in World Cup Tie </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRASILIA, June 28 (Xinhua) -- Brazil and Uruguay fought to a 1-
1 draw in a qualifying game for the 2002 World Cup in Rio de
Janeiro.
</P>
<P>
The Uruguayans, with a well-organized defense, kept Brazil at a
safe distance from the net during much of the first half.
</P>
<P>
Six minutes into action, Uruguayan striker Dario Silva sprinted
down the left side of the field to face Brazilian defender Aldair,
who slipped and fell to the ground. Silva easily sidestepped him
and fired the ball into the net.
</P>
<P>
Two minutes later, midfielder O'Neill nearly picked up Uruguay'
s second goal with a powerful shot, but the ball nicked the
crossbar.
</P>
<P>
Brazil was saved from defeat by Uruguayan striker Coelho, who
grabbed Guilherme's jersey just as the Brazilian was about to
score and knocked him down to the ground. Colombian referee Oscar
Ruiz awarded Brazil a penalty, which midfielder Rivaldo converted
into the tying goal in the 85th minute.
</P>
<P>
Lineups:
</P>
<P>
Uruguay:
</P>
<P>
Fabian Carini, Washington Tais, Alejandro Lembo, Paolo Montero,
Dario Rodriguez, Gianni Guigou, Pablo Garcia , Fabian O'Neill (
Giocomazzi, 83rd minute), Nicolas Olivera , Alvaro Recoba (Coelho,
58th minute) and Dario Silva .
</P>
<P>
Brazil: Dida, Cafu, Antonio Carlos, Aldair, Roberto Carlos,
Emerson, Vampeta (Ze Roberto, 69th minute), Rivaldo, Ronaldinho
Gaucho (Alex, 46th minute), Savio (Guilherme, 46th minute) and
Franca.
</P>
