<HEADLINE> Myanmar Rejects WHO Report </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, June 29 (Xinhua) -- Myanmar has rejected a report on
world health for the year 2000 issued by the World Health
Organization (WHO) in Geneva on June 21, which ranks Myanmar near
the bottom of the list despite significant gains made by the
country's health system in recent years.
</P>
<P>
A press release of the Myanmar Ministry of Health available
here Thursday said the WHO report is highly objectionable, blaming
that unreliable methods have been employed to arrive at the
assessment.
</P>
<P>
Myanmar is aggrieved that its unrelenting efforts to improve
health system performance have not been given the recognition it
deserves but instead discredited, the press release stated,
charging that the report is an egregious misrepresentation of the
overall health system performance of Myanmar.
</P>
<P>
The press release also charged that compilations made by the
WHO in assessing the health system of performance of Myanmar are
biased deviation from the pertinent data published by the
government and are found to be unacceptable.
</P>
<P>
The press release vowed that Myanmar will proceed on its chosen
path of implementing all aspects of modern health service for the
benefit of all citizens. 
