<HEADLINE> 208 State Enterprises to Be Closed Down in Croatia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZAGREB, June 28 (Xinhua) -- The Croatian government will close
208 of its state enterprises, Croatian Radio and Television
announced Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
In all, these insolvent enterprises, with government
institutions as investors or owners, registered a loss of over 600
million kuna (about 75.9 million U.S. dollars) last year.
</P>
<P>
To phase out bankrupt companies could help save 1.5 million
kuna (190,000 dollars) in government spending each day, said
Croatian Radio and Television. It did not elaborate on what to do
with the more than 10,000 employees.
</P>
<P>
The decision was made following an examination of the
performance of over 888 state enterprises in the Balkan country.
Another 178 of the inquired, which hired more than 30,000 people
and lost about 1.5 billion kuna (190 million dollars) last year,
were reprieved from closure. 
</P>
