<HEADLINE> East China Province Draws More Overseas Funds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, June 29 (Xinhua) -- East China's Anhui Province, a major
grain producer of the country, has used a growing amount of
overseas investment this year.
</P>
<P>
Recent statistics show the province approved the establishment
of 83 overseas-funded enterprises during the first five months of
the year, with combined contractual overseas capital of 76.52
million U.S. dollars, jumping 172 percent.
</P>
<P>
These businesses are chiefly related with infrastructure,
agriculture, information technology, and machinery.
</P>
<P>
An official with the Anhui Provincial Foreign Trade and
Economic Cooperation Commission attributed the high growth to an
improved investment environment in the province.
</P>
<P>
Anhui has issued a series of new policies to attract overseas
business people since the beginning of last year, and they include
measures to protect the legitimate rights and interests of
overseas investors.
</P>
<P>
Special centers have been established across the province to
deal with complaints from overseas investors.
</P>
<P>
Last year saw the establishment of 199 overseas-funded
businesses in the province, with a combined contractual overseas
investment of 360 million U.S. dollars, a year-on-year increase of
31 percent.  
