<HEADLINE> Train Derailment Kills 14 in Indonesia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, June 29 (Xinhua) -- At least 14 people died and dozens
of others were injured when a cargo train derailed Wednesday at
Jembatan Tinggi in Indonesia's West Sumatra province, Antara news
agency reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
"Most of the victims were youths and school children," the
report quoted a local police as saying.
</P>
<P>
The victims, who had been clinging to the ill-fated train's
sides, were thrown away from it and some others were crushed
between carriages that crashed into each other, said the police.
</P>
<P>
The train, which was transporting coal, was heading for Kayu
Tanam in Padang Pariaman municipality from Padang Panjang. But it
came off the track in Tanah Datar district at 11:00 a.m. local
time.
</P>
<P>
The cause of the derailment remains unclear.  
</P>
