<BODY>
<HEADLINE> More Newspaper Groups Established in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, June 29 (Xinhua) -- The Zhejiang Daily Newspapers
Group was established here recently, bringing the number of
newspapers groups in China to 15.
</P>
<P>
The new group consists of Zhejiang Daily, a leading newspaper
in this east China province of Zhejiang, two magazines, a website
and five other local newspapers.
</P>
<P>
The move is part of China's effort to boost the development of
newspaper industry while building a socialist market economy.
</P>
<P>
With the forming of the group, the newspapers will provide
more and better information for the readership, said Chen Min'er,
legal person of the group.
</P>
<P>
He said that the newspaper's social influence and economic
benefits lie in readership and establishing such a group is the
best way to this end.
</P>
<P>
China's first two newspaper groups, Guangming Daily and
Economic Daily, were formed in June of 1998. 
</P>
</TEXT>
