<HEADLINE> Asia's Largest Cardboard Company to Be Built in East China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NINGBO, June 29 (Xinhua) -- Third-phase construction of a large
cardboard production center, Ningbo Zhonghua, will soon begin in
Ningbo, a coastal city in east China's Zhejiang Province.
</P>
<P>
The 1.4-billion-U.S.-dollar project is designed to produce 260,
000 tons of food packaging board, 300,000 tons of fancy paperboard,
and 440,000 tons of corrugated board annually.
</P>
<P>
The construction of the first two phases has cost some 480
million U.S. dollars and have a combined production capacity of
500,000 tons of cardboard a year.
</P>
<P>
The facility will become Asia's largest paper production center
when the third-phase construction is scheduled for completion in
2001. 
