<HEADLINE> Coelho quits as Portugal Coach after Semifinal Defeat </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
BRUSSELS, June 28 (Xinhua) -- Humberto Coelho will quit as
Portuguese coach after his team was beaten 2-1 by France in a
dramatic Euro 2000 semifinal on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
"From July 31 I will no longer be Portuguese coach. I think
now is a good time to let you know," he said after the match.
</P>
<P>
"We need time to prepare for the next battle to have a new
coach. I wish all the best to my successor."
</P>
<P>
Coelho's appointment in December 1997 caused an outcry because
a poor track record as a trainer had forced him to take up a
business career.
</P>
<P>
But after he successfully steered Portugal through to the
finals, Soccer Federation chief Gilberto Madail said his
controversial choice was vindicated.
</P>
<P>
Aged 50, Coelho was considered one of Europe's leading liberos
and picked up four Portuguese championship medals from his days
with Benfica between 1968-75. 
</P>
