<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-29 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Economic Boom Leaves U.S. Working Poor Behind: Report </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Poverty has grown in both overall number and as a percentage of
people employed full-time and year-round since 1973, according to
the Conference Board.
</P>
<P>
Close to 3% of all full-time workers are living under the
poverty line, defined as 13,000 U.S. dollars for a family of three,
in 1998, the latest year for which data is available, the Board
said in its new study.
</P>
<P>
"Including dependents, this could be upwards of 5 million
people," it said.
</P>
<P>
The study finds that poverty in the U.S. fell dramatically in
the 1960s and 1970s but "the lasting gains have not materialized
since".
</P>
<P>
Except for 1982 and 1983, when the economy was coming off a
recession, today's poverty rate among full-time workers is the
highest over the last quarter, the report added.
</P>
<P>
The 84-year-old Conference of Board in a non-profit
organization with a broad membership within and outside the U.S.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000629.0309 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-29 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Drought to Trigger Energy Price Increases in Romania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, June 29 (Xinhua) -- As well as the damage to
agriculture, the current drought in Romania could trigger
increases in the energy prices, if going on for another month, the
Romanian Minister of Trade and Industries Radu Bercenu said on
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
"The drought will pose energy problems since a great chunk of
the energy produced, about 2,000 MwH, is generated by water plants
at low costs. Because of the drought, the energy generated by
these plants decreases a lot, and this has a negative impact on
prices,"Berceanu said.
</P>
<P>
Energy prices are calculated as a median of the prices for
power generated by water plants, thermoplants and the power
produced by the Cernavoda nuclear plant.
</P>
<P>
"If the water plants generate just 1,000 MwH, instead of 2,000
MwH, at 15 U.S. dollars/MwH, the remainder 1,000 MwH will have to
be compensated for by thermal power at 50 dollars/MwH, which will
push the median upwards," Berceanu said.
</P>
<P>
Romania is suffering the worst drought in the past 50 years;
most of the crops in the eastern and southeastern parts are
expected to yield no harvest. The drought has brought till now a
direct economic loss of more than 2 billion U.S. dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000629.0310 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-29 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Private Sector in Romania Has Biggest Arrears </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, June 29 (Xinhua) -- The private sector has the
biggest volume of arrears in the Romanian economy, with a total of
61,000 billion lei (2.87 billion U.S. dollars), the local media
Thursday quoted a Finance Ministry official as saying.
</P>
<P>
Second in this classification of debts comes the sector of
mixed property (state and private), with 44,632 billion lei (2.10
billion U.S. dollars) worth of arrears. The state sector comes
last, with 40,335 billion lei (1.90 billion U.S. dollars), State
Secretary of the Finance Ministry Iosefina Morosanu added.
</P>
<P>
As for the state sector, the state secretary said it held 27.5
percent of the total arrears, 21 percent of the arrears to social
security contribution, 34.7 percent of the arrears accumulated to
the health insurance, 33.95 percent of the ones to the additional
pension, 42 percent of the arrears to the unemployment fund, 40
percent of the arrears to the state budget, 32 percent to the
local budgets, and 11 percent to bank credits.
</P>
<P>
According to her, the big volume of arrears in the private
sector is caused by delaying the payment of the duties to the
state and suppliers because of the private economic agents'
shortage of financial sources. More than half of the arrears in
the private sector are to suppliers and 21 percent to the state
budget.
</P>
<P>
To reduce the arrears, the Finance Ministry has taken measures
to improve the collection, to reschedule the outstanding payments
and to turn the debts to the state into shares, the official also
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
