<HEADLINE> Argentina, Chile Promote Border Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, June 29 (Xinhua) -- Argentina and Chile signed
Thursday at a meeting held in Rio Gallegos City an agreement on
the implementation of policies to promote the development of
border traffic.
</P>
<P>
The agreement was signed Thursday in Rio Gallegos, Argentina,
by Argentine consul in Punta Arenas, Chile, Julian Tettamanti and
his Chilean counterpart in Rio Gallegos, Argentina, Roberto
Cordero Pinilla.
</P>
<P>
The agreement stated the common will to facilitate the transit
in the border ports and to promote commercial ties between both
nations.
</P>
<P>
It also said that the use of the first card of regional border
traffic will be jointly implemented in February or March of 2001,
as a pilot test in the border ports located between the Argentine
city of Rio Turbio and the Chilean city of Puerto Natales.
</P>
<P>
It was also resolved to speed up the tourist and commercial
integration of the zone by keeping open the day around at least
two of the border ports of the region, from the days previous to
the Holy Week, on long weekends, and at vacation time and during
traditional national celebrations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
