<HEADLINE> Wall Street Stocks Fall On Profit Warnings </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, June 29 (Xinhua) -- Wall Street stocks fell broadly
Thursday as profit warnings added to the market uncertainty after
the Federal Reserve indicated the need for one more hike in
interest rates if risk of inflation is coming.
</P>
<P>
The Dow Jones industrial average closed down 129.75 at 10,398.
04 and the technology heavy Nasdaq composite index fell 63.11 at 3,
877.23.
</P>
<P>
Broader stock indicators were mostly lower. The Standard &AMP; Poor
's 500 index fell 12.43 at 1,442.39.
</P>
<P>
Stocks fell as a number of companies announced separately that
their earnings will miss analysts' expectations in the second
quarter. Among them were Unisys and Goodyear.
</P>
<P>
The announcements hurt the market which was already cooled off
by the warnings of inflation from the Federal Reserve at the end
of policy-making meeting Wednesday. The warnings led investors to
believe that the Federal Reserve would raise rates again at the
August 22 meeting if the danger of inflation is increasing.
</P>
<P>
J.P. Morgan and Citigroup on the financial sector fell. LSI
Logic and Cisco on the technology side were also lower.
</P>
<P>
The Federal Reserve decided to leave rate unchanged Wednesday
after six hikes in rates in the past year in an effort to cool off
the U.S. economy and keep inflation under control. Analysts did
not rule out the possibility of one more action on rates following
the Federal Reserve's warning of inflation.
</P>
<P>
The NYSE index fell 1.46 at 642.75 and the Russell 2000 index
of smaller companies fell 8.41 at 512.58. But the American Stock
Exchange index rose 1.72 at 939.43.
</P>
<P>
Declining issues outnumbered advancers by a 10-to-9 margin on
the New York Stock Exchange, with 1,510 down, 1,452 up and 412
unchanged.
</P>
<P>
NYSE volume increased to 1.10 billion shares from 1.05 billion
in the previous session. 
</P>
